<i>Posted by aoenla on 04-09-2001 05:15 PM:</i>

<p><b> The RNG is actually fine, if you actually test it...</b></p>

<p>I won't bother to repeat the entire thread, but this topic recently came up in the Tunare server EZBoard forums, where some folks felt that they were always getting bad rolls, and that the random number generator was poor.  Specifically, the thread got started when the originator stated his belief that when randoming in small ranges, i.e. 1 to 4 or something to assign loot amongst 4 players, that the value "1" came up much more frequently than any other.  That set of several rather interesting tests, the upshot of which - the RNG verant is using is pretty good.<br>
<br>
Here's the thread, if you care to read it:<br>
<br>
<a href="http://pub13.ezboard.com/ftunaredragonsandplanes.showMessage?topicID=7239.topic" target="_blank">http://pub13.ezboard.com/ftunaredra...icID=7239.topic</a><br>
