<i>Posted by Calador Stormblood on 04-09-2001 05:58 PM:</i>

<p><b><img src="images/icons/icon3.gif" alt="Lightbulb" width="15" height="15" border="0"> Possible Seeding</b></p>

<p>I read a post somewhere a while back where some guy was claiming that Verant used /loc result to seed the random number generator (this would make sense, as it would give a fairly random seed).  He went on to explain his reasoning for this claim.  He had found spots in a couple dungeons where spell casting was nearly impossible, recorded the /loc, and then had another caster move to that spot and repeat his test.  It was fairly indicative that usage of /loc for seeding was in fact the case, as several casters who tried the spot found themselves fizzling 7-8 times per 10 casting attempts.<br>
<br>
So perhaps if you get a bad roll, make sure you move a little before your next one.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
