<i>Posted by Kivor on 04-10-2001 05:51 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>This is similar to a linear feedback shift register (I've made a post on this before), here's a quick read...<br>
<a href="http://www.rsasecurity.com/rsalabs/faq/2-1-5-1.html" target="_blank">http://www.rsasecurity.com/rsalabs/faq/2-1-5-1.html</a><br>
<br>
Seemingly random numbers made in this manner are not random at all. Simple software RNGs (such as rand(), seeded with srand()) operate much like this.<FONT face="arial, helvetica" size="2"><br>
