<i>Posted by Blackgoat on 04-10-2001 06:08 AM:</i>

<p><b> </b></p>

<p>One system someone told me was used for random numbers was that the computer took numbers from the clock...like the one one millionth place digit (if it is 4:32pm, the die might be the number that comes from 4:32.364272pm....and it being the last 2).  Simple system seems to me.  If you take say the last 4 digits from the thousanth place on down (4272) and then divide by some factor to generate a number from one to X instead of from zero to 9999, you have your die roll system.</p>


